The city was returned to Austria in 1814 and retored to Hungary in 1822, became part of the Croatian Crownland in 1848 and so remained until 1870 when it was given again t Hungary as an autonomous region.  From 1814 to 1870 despite changes in administration the postal regulations remained Austrian. When Austrian stamps were introduced in Austria in 1850, they were also used in Fiume. Hungarian stamps were not introduced until 1 May 1871 and their validity ceased after 31 July 1871. The enat Austrian postmarks provide an intereting chapter, as do letters with the Hungarian litho and recess issues of 1871. 

